OWERRI – The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has decried the flagrant violation of COVID-19 guidelines and over speeding by motorists during the yuletide as ma­jor challenges confronting road transportation in the country. Zonal Commanding Of­ficer, RS9 Enugu, Owoima­ha Odoma, disclosed this to newsmen in Owerri, the Imo Sate capital. Odoma said the issue had become worrisome as over speeding often had led to road crashes, while vio­lation of COVID-19 proto­col by motorists could also escalate the dreaded virus in various communities. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Udoma, who was on zonal inspection to enforce FRSC ‘Operation Zero Tol­erance to Road Traffic Vi­olation’, warned motorists against overspending. He said: “We embarked on road monitoring in the states under the zone and we have observed that speed violation, violation of Covid-19 guidelines were the major challenges on the road during this pe­riod.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION